u+v=\frac{30}{3 \sqrt{2}}
\end{array} \Leftrightarrow\right.\right.\right. \\
& \Leftrightarrow\left\{\begin{array}{l}
u-v=3 \sqrt{2}, \\
u+v=5 \sqrt{2},
\end{array} \text { from which } u=4 \sqrt{2}, v=\sqrt{2} .\right.
\end{aligned}
$$

Thus, $\left\{\begin{array}{l}\sqrt{x y^{2}}=4 \sqrt{2}, \\ \sqrt{x^{2} y}=\sqrt{2}\end{array} \Leftrightarrow\left\{\begin{array}{l}x y^{2}=32, \\ x^{2} y=2 .\end{array}\right.\right.$

